Reasoning: The paper deals with analyzing the spatial and temporal characteristics of web search engine results using IP addresses. This involves techniques such as geolocation and cartographic design. Based on these aspects, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
